humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, multiple left axillary sentinel lymph nodes were excised and were negative for tumor (AJCC pNO). The immunohistochemical cytokeratin stain also confirmed the absence of tumor in the sentinel lymph nodes. Therefore, based on the new rules 10 and 11, the N stage for this patient is N0, as all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma and there is no metastatic carcinoma in sentinel lymph nodes and regional lymph nodes.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states that multiple (2) left axillary sentinel lymph nodes are negative for tumor (AJCC pNO). This indicates that there is no evidence of cancer in the sentinel lymph nodes, which corresponds to an N0 stage.
